# Lab 11 ChatGPT Script Summary
# -------------------------------------------------------------
# This script recreates the FigTree visualization (Figure 21)
# of a BEAST MCC phylogenetic tree using R.
#
# Because FigTree could not be run, the workflow was rebuilt using:
# - treeio: to read the BEAST tree and preserve metadata
# - ggtree: to generate plotting coordinates (x, y)
# - ggplot2: to draw the tree manually
# - dplyr/tibble: to manipulate and combine data
# - ape: to reorder the tree (ladderize)
#
# Key steps:
# 1. Read the BEAST tree including posterior and HPD information.
# 2. Extract metadata (posterior values and 95% HPD intervals).
# 3. Obtain plotting coordinates from ggtree.
# 4. Join metadata with plotting coordinates by node.
# 5. Transform the x-axis so tips are at 0 and the tree is shown
#    as "time before present".
# 6. Rebuild branch segments manually using parent-child relationships.
# 7. Plot:
#    - tree structure (black lines)
#    - 95% HPD intervals (blue bars)
#    - posterior support values at internal nodes
#    - species labels at tips
#
# Interpretation:
# - Branching pattern shows relationships among primates.
# - Posterior values indicate support for each clade.
# - Blue bars represent uncertainty (95% HPD) in node ages.
# - X-axis represents time before present.
#
# Overall, this script reproduces the same information shown in FigTree,
# but using R for full control over plotting and data handling.
# -------------------------------------------------------------